TITLE: Defining Parametric Routes with Regular Expressions in Fastify (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define a GET route where a URL parameter (`:file`) must match a specific regular expression (`^\\d+`). Slashes within the regex must be escaped. The captured parameter value is accessed via `request.params`. Note that regex routes can be computationally expensive.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/main/docs/Reference/Routes.md#2025-04-22_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// parametric with regexp
fastify.get('/example/:file(^\\d+).png', function (request, reply) {
  // curl ${app-url}/example/12345.png
  // file === '12345'
  const { file } = request.params;
  // your code here
})
```

