TITLE: Using Async/Await in Route Handlers (Return Value) in Fastify (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates defining an `async` route handler in Fastify. It shows how asynchronous operations (e.g., `getData`, `processData`) can be awaited. Returning the final result directly automatically sends the response payload, eliminating the need to explicitly call `reply.send()`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/main/docs/Reference/Routes.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
fastify.get('/', options, async function (request, reply) {
  const data = await getData()
  const processed = await processData(data)
  return processed
})
```

