TITLE: Responding Early from Fastify Hooks (onRequest/preHandler)
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to send a response from `onRequest` (callback style) and `preHandler` (async style) hooks before the route handler is executed. It highlights that `reply.send()` stops the hook chain. For async hooks, `return reply` is mandatory after calling `reply.send()` asynchronously to prevent the request from continuing.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/main/docs/Reference/Hooks.md#2025-04-22_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
fastify.addHook('onRequest', (request, reply, done) => {
  reply.send('Early response')
})

// Works with async functions too
fastify.addHook('preHandler', async (request, reply) => {
  setTimeout(() => {
    reply.send({ hello: 'from prehandler' })
  })
  return reply // mandatory, so the request is not executed further
// Commenting the line above will allow the hooks to continue and fail with FST_ERR_REP_ALREADY_SENT
})
```

