TITLE: Implementing API Versioning with Route Prefixing in Fastify (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Shows the main server file (`server.js`) demonstrating how to register separate route modules (`./routes/v1/users`, `./routes/v2/users`) under different URL prefixes (`/v1`, `/v2`) using the `prefix` option in `fastify.register()`. This is a common pattern for API versioning without modifying individual route paths within the modules.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/main/docs/Reference/Routes.md#2025-04-22_snippet_13

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
// server.js
const fastify = require('fastify')()

fastify.register(require('./routes/v1/users'), { prefix: '/v1' })
fastify.register(require('./routes/v2/users'), { prefix: '/v2' })

fastify.listen({ port: 3000 })
```

