TITLE: Setting Custom Error Handler in Fastify
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to configure a custom error handler in Fastify that will be called whenever an error occurs. The example demonstrates logging the error and sending a custom 409 response.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/main/docs/Reference/Server.md#2025-04-22_snippet_37

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
fastify.setErrorHandler(function (error, request, reply) {
  // Log error
  this.log.error(error)
  // Send error response
  reply.status(409).send({ ok: false })
})
```

