TITLE: Adding and Referencing Shared JSON Schemas in Fastify (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to add a reusable JSON Schema to a Fastify instance using the addSchema API and reference it in route schema validation. Dependencies include Fastify and JSON Schema Draft 7. The example demonstrates referencing specific schema properties with $ref and setting up route validation for POST requests, expecting an array of objects conforming to the shared definition. Required properties, object structure, and validation scope are highlighted.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/main/docs/Reference/Validation-and-Serialization.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: JavaScript
CODE:
```
fastify.addSchema({
  $id: 'http://example.com/',
  type: 'object',
  properties: {
    hello: { type: 'string' }
  }
})

fastify.post('/', {
  handler () {},
  schema: {
    body: {
      type: 'array',
      items: { $ref: 'http://example.com#/properties/hello' }
    }
  }
})
```

