TITLE: Defining Routes with Multiple Parameters in a Single Segment in Fastify (JavaScript)
DESCRIPTION: Illustrates defining a GET route with multiple parameters (`:lat`, `:lng`) within the same URL path segment, separated by a specific character (a hyphen `-` in this case). Parameters are accessed individually from the `request.params` object.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/main/docs/Reference/Routes.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
fastify.get('/example/near/:lat-:lng/radius/:r', function (request, reply) {
  // curl ${app-url}/example/near/15째N-30째E/radius/20
  // lat === "15째N"
  // lng === "30째E"
  // r ==="20"
  const { lat, lng, r } = request.params;
  // your code here
})
```

