TITLE: Implementing Version Constraints for Fastify Routes
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to use version constraints to create multiple handlers for the same HTTP route path, matched according to the request's Accept-Version header. This follows semver specifications for route matching.
SOURCE: https://github.com/fastify/fastify/blob/main/docs/Reference/Routes.md#2025-04-22_snippet_23

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
fastify.route({
  method: 'GET',
  url: '/',
  constraints: { version: '1.2.0' },
  handler: function (request, reply) {
    reply.send({ hello: 'world' })
  }
})

fastify.inject({
  method: 'GET',
  url: '/',
  headers: {
    'Accept-Version': '1.x' // it could also be '1.2.0' or '1.2.x'
  }
}, (err, res) => {
  // { hello: 'world' }
})
```

